{
  "texts": [
    "Even though both FST and RST frameworks provide insights into how a supply chain may fall apart, reverse stress testing answers a different set of questions about the conditions under which a supply chain may degrade.",
    "While FST can build a catalog of \"what if\" scenarios for managers based on designed shock scenario simulations, RST averts the burden of scenario design and provides a threat-agnostic way to view a supply chain's resilience.",
    "RST focuses on the end user's concerns without being limited by the imagination of what could go wrong.",
    "It directly searches the infinite space of \"what ifs\" and finds the configurations and dynamics that can lead to untenable disruptions.",
    "Because of its ability to identify probable sources of disruption before they happen, RST more directly assesses the risk and resilience of a supply chain."
  ]
}